Run Flows in Bot User Context (Release Update)

With this update enabled, a flow initiated by a bot runs in user context. The user profile and permission sets associated with the bot determine object permissions and field-level access of the flow.

This change applies to Lightning Experience and Salesforce Classic in Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer editions.

Salesforce enforces this update in Winter ’25.

To get the major release upgrade date for your instance, go to Trust Status. This update improves security by preventing bots from creating or modifying records they don’t have access to.

Before enabling this update in production, test your bots that run flows with this update enabled in a sandbox or developer org.
title: Run Flows in Bot User Context Update
